g.text: It is Friday. At the end of her lessons
Giulia decides to spend some time in
the university museum before returning
home because being surrounded by art
makes her feel better.
Walking through the museum she
realizes that the layout has changed
since the last time she went there.
Upon entering the museum, she notices
a sign that talks about a new app,
iMuseum, designed to improve the
visitorâ€™s experience.
Thanks to the new layout she spots a
beautiful statue she had never noticed
before.
Giulia downloads the app and starts her
visit.
As soon as she approaches the statue
the app shows her all the information
about it.
Giulia spends several minutes reading
every single detail, being incredibly
fascinated.
Giulia continues her tour of the museum
discovering, thanks to the app, new
things also on the statues she had
already admired multiple times in her
previous visits.
Giulia leaves the museum amazed and
happy to have enriched her cultural
background.
NOTE: In this storyboard are used images from www.freevector.com and www.freepik.com designed by macrovector, Freepik
and FreeVector.
